x^2+19x+92
\bf{My\; Solution::}
x^2+19x+92 = k^2\;,
x,k\in \mathbb{Z}
x^2+19x+(92-k^2)=0
\displaystyle x = \frac{-19\pm \sqrt{19^2-4(92-k^2)}}{2} = \frac{-19\pm \sqrt{4k^2-7}}{2}
\displaystyle 4k^2-7 = 0\Rightarrow k=\pm \frac{\sqrt{7}}{2}
\eqalign{   y^2=x^2+19x+92\quad   &\Leftrightarrow\quad 4y^2=4x^2+38x+368=(2x+19)^2+7\cr   &\Leftrightarrow\quad 4y^2-(2x+19)^2=7\cr   &\Leftrightarrow\quad (2y-2x-19)(2y+2x+19)=7\cr}
\left(x + \frac{19}{2}\right)^2 + 92 - \left(\frac{19}{2}\right)^2 = k^2
